The paper deals with the fundamental graph primitive of triangle enumeration, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) another likely category. The paper mentions algorithms and computational models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses lower and upper bounds, which are concepts in graph theory and optimization, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
